What are your thoughts on
```suggestion
noncomputable def cauchyBound (p : K[X]) : ℝ≥0 :=
  sup (range p.natDegree) (fun x ↦ ‖p.coeff x‖₊) / ‖p.leadingCoeff‖₊
```
which avoids the `if` and the `sup'`?
I tried switching to `NNReal`, I think it's an improvement, except for `NNReal.geom_sum`, which should be moved to a different file. Do you know of a good place for it?

```suggestion
  field_simp [(tsub_pos_of_lt h).ne']
```
though I'm not sure it's a good idea to have rigid code after `field_simp`, so alternatively
```suggestion
  apply eq_div_of_mul_eq (tsub_pos_of_lt h).ne'
```
This file name seems too generic and the location too high up in the tree as well.
I'll rename it to `CauchyBound`. What would be a good location?

pullRequest.title: feat: prove Cauchy's upper bound on polynomial roots
